        The relationship is one that is built in terms of mutual respect, knowledge, trust. 
        Additionally, the doctor and patient's values and perspectives about disease, life,
         and time available play a role in building up this relationship. A strong relationship 
        between the doctor and patient will lead to frequent, quality information about the 
        patient's disease. Enhancing the accuracy of the diagnosis and increasing the patient's
         knowledge about the disease all come with a good relationship. 
